01:47.454 --> 01:49.571
Good day, ladies and gentlemen.

01:49.622 --> 01:51.073
This is Robert Hodge,

01:51.124 --> 01:53.542
United States Attorney
for the Southern District,

01:53.576 --> 01:56.411
speaking to you here in New York City.

01:56.413 --> 02:00.382
My fellow citizens, we are at war.

02:00.416 --> 02:03.385
Not against a foreign potentate.

02:03.419 --> 02:06.338
Not against a bloodthirsty despot.

02:06.389 --> 02:09.475
We are at war against an army of hoodlums

02:09.508 --> 02:13.595
who have made our streets
unsafe for decent people.

02:13.680 --> 02:16.648
Fear, intimidation,

02:16.683 --> 02:18.934
violence...

02:18.985 --> 02:22.604
these are the tools of
this nefarious scoundrel

02:22.606 --> 02:26.275
known as the modern-day criminal.

02:28.278 --> 02:30.445
From the Lower East Side to Harlem,

02:30.497 --> 02:32.114
Brooklyn to New Jersey,

02:32.116 --> 02:36.285
stretching as far south as Atlantic City.

02:36.287 --> 02:39.121
Bloodshed and mayhem are the currency

02:39.172 --> 02:42.457
of these reprobates,
thugs, and bootleggers...

02:43.877 --> 02:48.847
as they struggle for control
of our nation's streets.

02:50.166 --> 02:53.101
Both Governor Roosevelt
and I remain committed

02:53.136 --> 02:56.471
to this battle, which we must and will win.

02:57.974 --> 03:01.310
Together, with the officers of
Police Commissioner Mulrooney

03:01.361 --> 03:03.478
and District Attorney Crain,

03:03.480 --> 03:06.865
my staff and I are working round the clock

03:06.900 --> 03:09.318
to make certain these cowards

03:09.369 --> 03:10.786
are brought to justice.

03:12.071 --> 03:14.323
I give you my solemn word

03:14.374 --> 03:18.961
that I shall not rest till
every man, woman, and child

03:18.995 --> 03:22.965
can once again safely walk our streets.

03:22.999 --> 03:25.000
This has been Robert Hodge

03:25.051 --> 03:27.669
broadcasting from New York City.

03:42.569 --> 03:44.653
19 men dead between us,

03:44.687 --> 03:46.188
at least a million in lost revenue,

03:46.190 --> 03:47.689
and no goddamn end in sight.

03:47.691 --> 03:49.575
Calm, Mr. Thompson.

03:49.609 --> 03:51.693
Yes, you've been saying that for weeks.

03:51.695 --> 03:55.581
Like all impetuous children,
Luciano will make a mistake.

03:55.615 --> 03:58.367
And while we're waiting,
how are we supposed to eat?

03:58.369 --> 04:01.119
- Hey, Nuck.
- What?

04:01.170 --> 04:02.671
12 of our trucks were firebombed.

04:02.705 --> 04:04.923
Nearly 100 grand up in smoke.

04:07.211 --> 04:09.761
God fucking damn it!

04:10.964 --> 04:14.716
You had mentioned Mr. Capone in Chicago.

04:14.718 --> 04:16.267
Perhaps with additional support...

04:16.302 --> 04:18.887
He's cut me loose. Don't you get it?

04:18.889 --> 04:20.639
We're on our own here.

04:20.690 --> 04:22.858
All that happens, happens as it should.

04:22.892 --> 04:24.359
Then why see a doctor, Sal?

04:24.394 --> 04:26.361
Why get out of the way
of an oncoming train?

04:26.396 --> 04:28.313
Why get out of the
fucking bed in the morning?

04:29.782 --> 04:32.034
I'm counseling restraint.

04:32.068 --> 04:34.152
We are playing a game of chess.

04:34.203 --> 04:37.489
I've played chess and I've never
had an opponent try to kill me.

04:37.573 --> 04:39.291
I'm counseling action.

04:39.325 --> 04:41.994
As in stringing this Luciano
up by his fucking ball sack.

04:42.045 --> 04:45.881
You're tired. Understandably so.

04:45.915 --> 04:48.250
As am I.

04:48.252 --> 04:50.836
I will send more men to guard your trucks.

04:50.887 --> 04:53.422
And in the meantime, if
Luciano shows a hair...

04:53.473 --> 04:55.090
I will cut it.

04:55.092 --> 04:57.509
Along with his fucking throat.

05:01.648 --> 05:03.315
Car's ready, Mr. Maranzano.

05:03.349 --> 05:04.483
Gave it a good scrubbing.

05:04.517 --> 05:06.268
Got the bugs off your windscreen.

05:06.319 --> 05:08.236
Bravo, picciotto.

05:08.271 --> 05:11.440
So we may all see clearly the road ahead.

05:16.863 --> 05:18.330
Tired of waiting on him.

05:18.364 --> 05:21.199
Oh, no, that's okay. My pleasure.

05:21.250 --> 05:24.002
Really, but thank you.

05:29.425 --> 05:31.343
We talked about last night.

05:33.930 --> 05:36.348
Aren't you the kid told me he was hungry?

05:36.382 --> 05:38.517
Doing okay now.

05:40.019 --> 05:42.971
Fill your gut a lot quicker
with this than a shammy.

05:44.440 --> 05:45.807
How's that make you feel?

05:45.809 --> 05:48.060
What are you doing?

05:48.111 --> 05:49.945
It's all hands on deck, ain't it?

05:51.130 --> 05:53.615
You're not part of this, you understand?

05:54.867 --> 05:57.486
Take Archie and Sean, head to New York.

05:57.488 --> 05:58.987
For what?

06:00.823 --> 06:03.992
I could be impetuous myself.

06:29.318 --> 06:32.354
Oh, if it ain't the
macher of Willett Street.

06:32.356 --> 06:33.655
Your husband around?

06:33.689 --> 06:35.857
He went to Aqueduct for the morning.

06:35.859 --> 06:38.693
Then I'll just grab what I came for.

07:39.305 --> 07:40.505
And the book.

07:40.556 --> 07:42.841
I bought the book.

07:42.892 --> 07:44.793
With what?

07:44.827 --> 07:46.178
The money I had.

07:46.229 --> 07:49.297
Where'd you get the money?

07:49.332 --> 07:50.999
You can't prove it.

07:51.033 --> 07:53.685
I don't have to prove it, you do.

07:53.736 --> 07:55.904
That's not how the law works.

07:58.774 --> 08:00.942
Give it to me anyway.

08:12.040 --> 08:13.420
_

08:13.422 --> 08:14.923
You have a library?

08:14.957 --> 08:17.559
- Yes.
- How many books?

08:17.593 --> 08:19.561
Just that one for now.

08:19.595 --> 08:21.596
But it's the proper thing to do.

08:22.798 --> 08:24.933
Who taught you that? Your mother?

08:27.687 --> 08:29.771
Everybody comes from somewhere.

08:29.805 --> 08:31.840
Where do you come from?

08:31.874 --> 08:33.692
From here.

08:34.977 --> 08:37.979
Born here. Family's here.

08:38.014 --> 08:39.865
Where's your family?

08:39.899 --> 08:42.384
It's rude to ask personal questions.

08:42.418 --> 08:45.053
I'm sorry to offend you.

08:45.087 --> 08:47.072
But here's our situation.

08:47.123 --> 08:49.457
- You stole all these things.
- I didn't...

08:49.492 --> 08:51.543
Except for the book.

08:51.577 --> 08:53.795
A legal scholar such as yourself

08:53.829 --> 08:56.631
should know that's called larceny.

08:56.666 --> 08:58.934
You've been sleeping on the boardwalk.

08:58.968 --> 09:00.335
That's vagrancy.

09:00.386 --> 09:02.671
So I could put you in a cell

09:02.722 --> 09:05.891
and you can sit there
until you decide to talk.

09:05.925 --> 09:09.344
Or I could help you.

09:11.614 --> 09:13.915
Why would you do that?

09:13.950 --> 09:17.085
You look like you might need help.

09:21.107 --> 09:23.441
Where are your parents?

09:26.796 --> 09:28.530
Who looks after you?

09:30.132 --> 09:32.834
Where did you learn what's proper?

09:36.038 --> 09:38.690
915 Haddon Avenue.

09:38.724 --> 09:41.209
There's no Haddon Avenue in Atlantic City.

09:41.211 --> 09:43.011
It's in Trenton.

09:43.045 --> 09:44.763
Whose house is that?

09:44.797 --> 09:47.182
Nobody's house.

09:47.216 --> 09:49.384
Is it a school?

09:53.456 --> 09:55.657
Is it an orphanage?

09:57.893 --> 10:00.228
My name is in that book.

10:00.263 --> 10:02.030
If you take it, you're stealing from me

10:02.064 --> 10:04.232
and you're certainly no gentleman.

10:14.076 --> 10:16.461
I need you to pull all
the prostitution cases

10:16.495 --> 10:17.963
north of 110th Street.

10:17.997 --> 10:19.581
You need me to?

10:19.583 --> 10:21.299
Mr. Hodge does.

10:21.334 --> 10:23.084
Right.

10:24.503 --> 10:26.972
I'm sorry, okay? I don't
make the assignments.

10:27.006 --> 10:28.757
Would it be any different if you did?

10:28.808 --> 10:30.175
Yes.

10:30.226 --> 10:32.927
I know you're good at your job.

10:32.929 --> 10:34.763
Mr. Hodge does, too.

10:34.765 --> 10:36.398
It's just...

10:36.432 --> 10:38.933
you have to admit this
is all a little sensitive

10:38.935 --> 10:40.435
given your family background.

10:40.486 --> 10:41.853
Sensitive?

10:41.904 --> 10:44.356
What is that code for?
Thompson can't be trusted?

10:44.407 --> 10:46.908
If anyone felt like that,
you'd have been fired by now.

10:46.942 --> 10:49.577
- Thompson.
- Or never hired in the first place.

10:49.612 --> 10:51.279
Thompson.

10:51.281 --> 10:53.948
- Call for you.
- All right.

10:57.003 --> 10:59.954
Ahem, Thompson.

11:01.290 --> 11:02.674
Hello?

11:02.708 --> 11:05.760
Hey, Willie, it's your father.

11:05.795 --> 11:07.796
Where are you?

11:07.798 --> 11:10.131
I'm in town.

11:10.133 --> 11:11.716
What are you doing?

11:11.767 --> 11:14.352
I just flew into town
and I was wondering if...

11:14.387 --> 11:15.804
No, I can't.

11:15.855 --> 11:17.639
Maybe...

11:17.641 --> 11:19.057
No, I can't.

11:19.108 --> 11:20.859
I understand. I was just thinking...

11:20.893 --> 11:23.028
I...

11:24.113 --> 11:25.447
Not till this evening.

11:25.481 --> 11:28.650
Okay. Okay.

11:33.906 --> 11:35.990
Everything okay?

11:40.162 --> 11:42.497
Let me get you the rest of those files.

11:49.922 --> 11:52.974
It's an orphanage in Trenton.

11:53.008 --> 11:55.977
Doesn't seem to be a telephone.

11:56.011 --> 11:57.429
I can bring her back tomorrow,

11:57.480 --> 11:59.898
but it will be most of
the day coming and going.

11:59.932 --> 12:02.016
Why did she run off?

12:02.018 --> 12:04.119
I couldn't get it out of her.

12:04.153 --> 12:05.854
Sounds rather harsh.

12:05.856 --> 12:09.407
I didn't do anything. I brought her here.

12:11.110 --> 12:13.111
She must have a reason.

12:13.162 --> 12:15.780
Everyone has a reason.

12:15.831 --> 12:17.665
Murderers have reasons.

12:17.700 --> 12:21.252
You said she stole cigarettes.

12:21.287 --> 12:23.588
I just mean you can only
help someone so much.

12:23.622 --> 12:26.374
Who are you trying to persuade?

12:28.294 --> 12:30.311
I'll take her back in the morning.

12:30.346 --> 12:31.963
It's all I can do.

12:32.932 --> 12:34.799
If that's how you see it.

12:34.850 --> 12:36.434
What do you want from me?

12:36.469 --> 12:38.219
What do you want from yourself?

12:38.270 --> 12:39.637
I'm tr...

12:39.688 --> 12:41.940
I'm trying to do the right thing here.

12:43.943 --> 12:46.394
I haven't even had supper yet.

12:53.452 --> 12:55.403
Next time, get here earlier.

12:55.405 --> 12:57.322
You won't have to work so fast.

12:57.373 --> 12:59.040
Then I'd have to talk to you.

12:59.074 --> 13:01.409
Mayn kleyne farbrekher.

13:13.005 --> 13:14.422
- Hey, Talia.
- What?

13:14.473 --> 13:16.307
I think I left my tongue down there.

13:31.073 --> 13:33.441
Ben Siegel. I can't believe it.

13:33.492 --> 13:35.276
Hey, Morris.

13:37.079 --> 13:38.830
What brings you to the neighborhood?

13:38.864 --> 13:42.116
Schnorrer upstairs owes me money.

13:42.168 --> 13:44.786
Feigenbaum? Ah, he's a prick and a half.

13:44.788 --> 13:46.621
I don't name names.

13:48.040 --> 13:50.041
John Hancock for my wife?

13:50.092 --> 13:52.126
Everybody knows who you are.

13:52.128 --> 13:54.512
Sure thing. Clara, right?

13:54.547 --> 13:55.930
Talia.

13:55.965 --> 13:57.849
I'm thinking of my aunt.

13:57.883 --> 14:00.718
My pop, your pop, same
minyan at Bialystoker.

14:00.769 --> 14:02.303
Yeah, he's praying for both of us.

14:02.305 --> 14:03.855
Oh!

14:03.889 --> 14:05.473
Like that joke, right?

14:05.475 --> 14:06.941
Rich man and a poor man.

14:06.976 --> 14:09.060
And they're both davening at the same...

14:10.312 --> 14:12.647
Look who it is. Look, Ben Siegel.

14:12.698 --> 14:14.983
Talk about bad pennies.

14:15.034 --> 14:16.985
Why you got to be like that for?

14:16.987 --> 14:19.320
With you, it's always crepe-hanging.

14:19.322 --> 14:21.406
This is an important person.

14:21.457 --> 14:23.958
And please, put on a dress.
It's the middle of the day.

14:23.993 --> 14:25.126
What are you...

14:31.500 --> 14:33.418
Oh, fuck!

14:33.469 --> 14:35.253
Manténlo vivo.

14:35.304 --> 14:38.223
Manténlo vivo! Alive!

14:38.257 --> 14:39.757
Alive!

14:47.850 --> 14:49.317
Yeah.

14:49.351 --> 14:51.352
What the hell's going on?

14:59.361 --> 15:01.996
Stop shooting, you fucking moron!

15:05.251 --> 15:07.168
It's quitting time, pal.

15:07.202 --> 15:09.370
Now, you and me...

15:09.372 --> 15:11.456
No!

15:12.925 --> 15:15.209
Oh, no. Don't.

15:18.213 --> 15:20.548
You come with me.

15:20.550 --> 15:22.383
I'm dying.

15:22.385 --> 15:24.352
So you're the one sliced off Tonino's ear?

15:24.386 --> 15:26.104
I'm dying.

15:26.138 --> 15:28.556
- That was some loopy shit.
- I'm dying.

15:28.558 --> 15:30.441
- Morris.
- What, do you keep 'em in your dresser?

15:30.476 --> 15:33.144
- Maybe I keep yours.
- Okay! Okay!

15:33.195 --> 15:34.862
- Okay.
- I'm dying, I'm dying.

15:34.897 --> 15:36.364
You're not dying.

15:36.398 --> 15:38.566
Who wants to go on living like this?

15:38.617 --> 15:40.118
Hey, Morris.

15:40.152 --> 15:43.371
Morris, abi gezunt, huh?

15:43.405 --> 15:45.573
Yeah.

15:47.543 --> 15:49.377
Ahem.

15:56.669 --> 15:58.753
What do you think?

15:58.755 --> 16:00.338
Very pretty.

16:00.389 --> 16:02.840
I wasn't quite so tall at her age,

16:02.891 --> 16:04.592
but better than cap and trousers.

16:04.594 --> 16:06.427
Yes, ma'am.

16:06.478 --> 16:08.479
We should get started.

16:08.514 --> 16:10.982
Oh, there's something she'd like to say.

16:11.016 --> 16:13.484
Yes?

16:13.519 --> 16:15.770
I wish to make amends.

16:15.821 --> 16:17.505
I beg your pardon?

16:17.539 --> 16:19.440
For the things I stole.

16:19.442 --> 16:21.826
And how would you do that?

16:21.860 --> 16:23.277
By working.

16:23.279 --> 16:24.946
Working where?

16:24.948 --> 16:26.864
She can help around the house.

16:26.915 --> 16:29.417
And I'll ask at the school.
I'm sure others can use her.

16:29.451 --> 16:31.419
She has to go back to Trenton.

16:32.621 --> 16:34.706
May I speak with you?

16:47.136 --> 16:48.970
You cannot leave her there.

16:48.972 --> 16:50.805
It's where she belongs.

16:50.807 --> 16:53.358
No child belongs there. It's brutish.

16:53.392 --> 16:54.809
You don't know that.

16:54.811 --> 16:57.645
- I know what she told me.
- She ran away.

16:57.696 --> 16:59.280
What do you expect her to say?

16:59.314 --> 17:01.449
That is my point exactly.

17:01.483 --> 17:05.153
She can't stay here.
We don't have the room.

17:05.204 --> 17:07.538
We don't have the money
and we don't have the right.

17:07.573 --> 17:09.156
I will find her a situation.

17:09.208 --> 17:11.626
Girls are always needed.

17:13.712 --> 17:15.997
She has no one.

17:15.999 --> 17:18.165
Children her age are not wanted.

17:18.167 --> 17:20.001
You can't stop every bad thing.

17:20.002 --> 17:22.753
Then why stop an... any of them?

17:25.174 --> 17:27.642
Your desire was to help.

17:27.675 --> 17:30.261
This is what helping means.

17:37.820 --> 17:39.404
Fanelli took a ride by the club.

17:39.438 --> 17:42.607
He didn't see hide nor hair
of Maranzano or his men.

17:42.658 --> 17:45.159
Probably hunkered down in the Bronx.

17:45.194 --> 17:47.495
He's working from his office,
the New York Central Building.

17:47.529 --> 17:49.030
Park Avenue.

17:49.032 --> 17:51.115
So we get one of the
Vanderbilt broads to ice him.

17:51.166 --> 17:54.035
Ahem. Benny's on the
line. Says it's important.

17:54.086 --> 17:56.204
100 bucks says it ain't.

17:58.590 --> 18:01.175
- Where the fuck are you?
- Atlantic City.

18:01.210 --> 18:04.045
- I've been kidnapped.
- God damn it, Benny.

18:04.047 --> 18:05.880
He's in Atlantic City.

18:05.882 --> 18:08.549
- With some skirt?
- Where else?

18:08.551 --> 18:09.884
Listen to me, you fucking numbskull.

18:09.935 --> 18:11.769
- Get your ass back here.
- Fuck you yelling at me for?

18:11.804 --> 18:14.138
I've been snatched, for Christ's
sakes. I'm practically killed.

18:14.189 --> 18:16.057
I don't care how great
a piece of ass she is.

18:16.108 --> 18:18.059
Get on the horn with this yentzer and...

18:20.145 --> 18:21.446
He hung up on me.

18:21.480 --> 18:22.730
Who did?

18:22.781 --> 18:24.115
- Charlie.
- Why?

18:24.149 --> 18:26.234
He's a fucking asshole.
What do you want from me?

18:31.406 --> 18:33.741
Is this for real?

18:33.792 --> 18:35.493
Oh, you want to play games now?

18:35.544 --> 18:37.411
- Don't hang up on me.
- Who's this?

18:37.463 --> 18:40.248
If you want to see your friend again,
you'll listen to me very carefully.

18:40.250 --> 18:41.799
I fucking told you I was kidnapped.

18:41.834 --> 18:43.084
Ah!

18:43.086 --> 18:45.503
Shut you fuck up.

18:45.554 --> 18:47.755
- You there?
- Put him on.

18:47.757 --> 18:49.807
He wants to talk to you.

18:49.842 --> 18:51.809
Hey, Charlie. What's cooking?

18:51.844 --> 18:53.594
- You all right?
- Sure.

18:53.596 --> 18:56.147
They took me to see the
diving horse and everything.

18:56.181 --> 18:57.932
Later on, we're getting cotton candy.

18:57.934 --> 18:59.267
I told you to be careful, didn't I?

18:59.318 --> 19:01.402
I got a bullet in my leg.
You gonna hock me now?

19:01.436 --> 19:03.604
Put Thompson back on.

19:07.609 --> 19:09.777
- I'm here.
- What do you want?

19:09.828 --> 19:12.113
A meeting so we can settle this bullshit.

19:12.164 --> 19:14.615
I'll meet you at your
funeral. We can talk there.

19:14.666 --> 19:16.501
You'll go to Siegel's before mine.

19:16.535 --> 19:20.087
Interesting proposition.
Let me think it over.

19:26.628 --> 19:28.763
You gonna be using that phone again?

19:28.797 --> 19:30.464
Why?

19:30.466 --> 19:32.133
I got to call Esther.

19:32.135 --> 19:34.468
It's Lag BaOmer tonight.
I said I'd be home.

19:34.520 --> 19:37.605
- Someone married you?
- Now you're talking shit about my wife?

19:37.639 --> 19:38.982
Just so happens

19:39.008 --> 19:40.191
I'm gonna be a father in a couple of weeks.

19:40.225 --> 19:42.226
- What's your decision?
- About what?

19:42.277 --> 19:43.528
I take that very seriously.

19:43.562 --> 19:46.564
- Margaret?
- Sure, I cat around.

19:46.615 --> 19:48.733
But a good woman waiting
for me? Never forget it.

19:48.784 --> 19:51.118
- Is something going on?
- Rehearsing an act downstairs.

19:51.153 --> 19:54.539
So any of you momzers rats me out
about being at that gash's apartment...

19:54.573 --> 19:56.574
- You wanted confirmation.
- Hold on.

19:56.625 --> 20:00.127
I swear to God, I'll pop a slug so
far up your ass, your back teeth...

20:06.001 --> 20:07.251
Say it again.

20:07.302 --> 20:09.921
You've shorted 50,000 shares

20:09.972 --> 20:11.923
of the Mayflower Grain Corporation.

20:11.974 --> 20:14.091
Short another 50,000 in the morning.

20:14.142 --> 20:16.310
You're being awfully curt.

20:16.345 --> 20:19.313
Sorry. Please short another 50,000.

20:19.348 --> 20:22.149
- It's a big position.
